value.value: The regulated release of dopamine from the somatodendritic compartment (cell body or dendrites) of a neuron.
The regulated release of dopamine from an axon.
The actin cytoskeleton that is part of a presynapse.
The intermediate filament cytoskeleton that is part of a postsynapse.

label.value: postsynaptic modulation of chemical synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process, acting in the postsynapse that results in modulation of chemical synaptic transmission.

label.value: presynaptic modulation of chemical synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process, acting in the presynapse that results in modulation of chemical synaptic transmission.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of trans-synaptic signaling.
The intermediate filament cytoskeleton that is part of a presynapse.
Fusion of the membrane of a vesicle with the plasma membrane, thereby releasing its contents into the extracellular space.
A cytoplasmic, membrane bound vesicle that is capable of fusing to the plasma membrane to release its contents into the extracellular space.
A polymer consisting of an indefinite number of protein or protein complex subunits that have polymerised to form a fiber-shaped structure.
A component of the cytoskeleton consisting of a homo or heteropolymeric fiber constructed from an indeterminate number of protein subunits.

label.value: G protein-coupled receptor activity involved in regulation of postsynaptic membrane potential

value.value: A G protein-coupled receptor activity occurring in the postsynaptic membrane that is part of a GPCR signaling pathway that positively regulates ion channel activity in the postsynaptic membrane.

label.value: presynaptic process involved in chemical synaptic transmission

value.value: The pathway leading to secretion of a neurotransmitter from the presynapse as part of synaptic transmission.
Cell-cell signaling to, from or within a synapse.
Cell-cell signaling in either direction across the synaptic cleft.

label.value: regulation of translation at synapse, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating translation occurring at the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: Cell-cell signaling between presynapse and postsynapse, across the synaptic cleft, that modulates the synaptic transmission properties of the synapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: The part of synaptic transmission occurring in the post-synapse: a signal transduction pathway consisting of neurotransmitter receptor activation and its effects on postsynaptic membrane potential and the ionic composition of the postsynaptic cytosol.
Any (proper) part of the cytoplasm of a single cell of sufficient size to still be considered cytoplasm.
The portion of the cytoskeleton contained within the presynapse.
The portion of the cytoskeleton contained within the postsynapse.

label.value: regulation of translation at presynapse, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating translation occurring at the presynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

label.value: regulation of translation at postsynapse, modulating synaptic transmission

value.value: Any process that modulates synaptic transmission by regulating translation occurring at the postsynapse.

definition.value: Note that this term was created for the SynGO project, and will be obsoleted when the SynGO annotations are made in Noctua.

value.value: Any signal release from a synapse.
The complete extent of cell cortex that underlies some some region of the plasma membrane.

label.value: regulation of skeletal muscle contraction by action potential

value.value: Any action potential process that regulates skeletal muscle contraction.

label.value: regulation of inflammatory response to wounding

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response to wounding.

label.value: negative regulation of inflammatory response to wounding

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response to wounding.

label.value: positive regulation of inflammatory response to wounding

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response to wounding.

Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving cobalamin (vitamin B12), a water-soluble vitamin characterized by possession of a corrin nucleus containing a cobalt atom.

label.value: positive regulation of cobalamin metabolic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a cobalamin metabolic process.

label.value: negative regulation of cobalamin metabolic process

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a cobalamin metabolic process.

label.value: positive regulation of animal organ morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of animal organ morphogenesis.

label.value: negative regulation of animal organ morphogenesis

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of animal organ morphogenesis.

A part of a cellular organism that is either an immaterial entity or a material entity with granularity above the level of a protein complex but below that of an anatomical system. Or, a substance produced by a cellular organism with granularity above the level of a protein complex.
A prolongation or process extending from a cell and that is bounded by plasma membrane, e.g. a cilium, lamellipodium, or axon.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Formation of a prolongation or process extending and that is bounded by plasma membrane, e.g. a cilium, lamellipodium, or axon.

label.value: regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly.

label.value: negative regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly.

label.value: positive regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of plasma membrane bounded cell projection assembly.

label.value: regulation of plasma membrane bounded cell projection organization

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of plasma membrane bounded cell projections.

label.value: plasma membrane bounded cell projection organization

value.value: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a plasma membrane bounded prolongation or process extending from a cell, e.g. a cilium or axon.
Contractions of the intestinal tract that include peristalsis (moving contents onward) and non-peristaltic movement (moving contents back and forth).
All of the contents of a plasma membrane bounded neuron projection, excluding the plasma membrane surrounding the projection.

The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of any steroid hormone, naturally occurring substances secreted by specialized cells that affects the metabolism or behavior of other cells possessing functional receptors for the hormone.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of bile acid from a cell or a tissue.

label.value: positive regulation of bile acid secretion

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of bile acid from a cell or a tissue.

label.value: negative regulation of bile acid secretion

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the controlled release of bile acid from a cell or a tissue.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the deposition or modulates the distribution of coloring matter in an organism.
